---
const faqs = [
  {
    q: 'Is it really free?',
    a: 'Yes. OrbitDMX is MIT licensed and free to download and use. No accounts, no telemetry, no paywalls.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What hardware do I need?',
    a: 'A desktop computer and an FTDI-based USB-DMX interface. OrbitDMX drives one DMX universe over that interface.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Which fixtures are supported?',
    a: 'A built-in library covers many AYRA fixtures plus generic RGB / RGBW / moving-head types. More profiles can be added.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Does it need internet or an account?',
    a: 'No. It runs fully offline. The only network call is an optional check for the latest version on this download page.',
  },
  {
    q: 'When can I buy an OrbitBridgeDeck?',
    a: 'It is still in development. The firmware is open source — follow the GitHub repo for progress.',
  },
];
---

<section id="faq" aria-labelledby="faq-title">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">FAQ</span>
      <hr class="divider" />
      <h2 id="faq-title">Questions</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-list">
      {faqs.map((f) => (
        <details class="faq-item reveal">
          <summary>{f.q}</summary>
          <p>{f.a}</p>
        </details>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .faq-list {
    max-width: 760px;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .faq-item {
    background: var(--bg-elevated);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 0 1.25rem;
  }

  summary {
    list-style: none;
    cursor: pointer;
    padding: 1.1rem 0;
    font-weight: 600;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }

  summary::after {
    content: '+';
    color: var(--accent-2);
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1;
    transition: transform 0.2s ease;
  }

  .faq-item[open] summary::after { transform: rotate(45deg); }

  .faq-item p {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0 0 1.2rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.96rem;
  }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    summary::after { transition: none; }
  }
</style>
